---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = "Why Work with a REALTOR | Buyer's Guide | Cody Posey";
const pageDescription = 'How a licensed REALTOR gives New Braunfels, TX homebuyers an advantage — fiduciary duty, negotiation, contract expertise, and local market knowledge that pays off.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/buyers-guide/why-use-a-realtor' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: "Buyer's Guide", url: '/buyers-guide' },
    { name: 'Why Use a REALTOR', url: '/buyers-guide/why-use-a-realtor' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="sub-hero">
      <div class="sub-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="sub-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/buyers-guide">Buyer's Guide</a> <span>/</span> <span>Why Use a REALTOR</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Why Work with a <span style="color:#FF1616;">REALTOR&reg;</span></h1>
        <p>The difference between an agent and a REALTOR&reg; matters</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="page-intro">Not all real estate practitioners are REALTORS&reg;. REALTORS&reg; are members of the national, state, and local associations of REALTORS&reg; and subscribe to a strict Code of Ethics. Here is why you should work with a REALTOR&reg;.</p>

        <div class="realtor-intro-detail">
          <p>The distinction between a real estate agent and a REALTOR&reg; matters more than most buyers realize. While any licensed agent can help you buy or sell a home, a REALTOR&reg; is held to a higher standard of professionalism and accountability. The National Association of REALTORS&reg; Code of Ethics covers duties to clients, duties to other REALTORS&reg;, and duties to the public. It requires honesty, transparency, and putting the client's interests above the agent's own.</p>
          <p>In a market like New Braunfels, where growth is happening rapidly and new developments are reshaping the landscape, having a REALTOR&reg; who understands the local market dynamics is essential. From knowing which subdivisions are in flood zones to understanding the differences between Comal ISD and New Braunfels ISD school boundaries, local expertise translates directly into better decisions for you as a buyer. A REALTOR&reg; who lives and works in the community can provide insights that no amount of online research can replace.</p>
          <p>Working with a REALTOR&reg; also means you have someone in your corner who is trained in contract negotiation, understands the legal requirements of Texas real estate transactions, and maintains ongoing education to stay current with market changes and regulations. Below are the key advantages of partnering with a REALTOR&reg; for your home purchase.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="realtor-grid">
          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14,2 14,8 20,8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Navigate a Complicated Process</h3>
            <p>A REALTOR&reg; understands the forms necessary and will help you avoid costly mistakes throughout the transaction. Real estate contracts in Texas are detailed and specific — having a professional who knows them inside and out protects your interests. The standard Texas residential contract alone is over a dozen pages, and there are multiple addenda that may apply depending on your situation, such as the third-party financing addendum, property condition addendum, and HOA addendum. Missing a deadline or misunderstanding a clause can cost you thousands of dollars or your earnest money deposit.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="2" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12"/><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 014 10 15.3 15.3 0 01-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 01-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 014-10z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Information &amp; Opinions</h3>
            <p>REALTORS&reg; can provide local community information on utilities, zoning, schools, and more to help you make informed decisions. They know the neighborhoods, the trends, and the details that don't show up in online listings. For example, a local REALTOR&reg; in New Braunfels can tell you about upcoming road projects, which areas tend to flood during heavy rains, where new commercial development is planned, and how different neighborhoods compare in terms of property tax rates and HOA fees.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"/><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Help Finding the Right Property</h3>
            <p>Your REALTOR&reg; will do the legwork to find the properties that suit your needs, budget, and lifestyle. Instead of scrolling through hundreds of listings, your agent curates options that match what you're actually looking for. REALTORS&reg; also have access to the MLS before many listings appear on public websites, and they often hear about homes coming to market through their professional network before they are officially listed. This early access can be a significant advantage in a competitive market.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Negotiating Skills</h3>
            <p>Your agent can advise you about many negotiating factors such as price, financing, terms, and date of possession. A skilled negotiator can save you thousands of dollars and protect you from unfavorable terms. Beyond price, your REALTOR&reg; negotiates the option period length, repairs after inspections, seller concessions toward closing costs, and even details like which appliances and fixtures stay with the home. Every element of the offer is an opportunity to protect your interests.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22,12 18,12 15,21 9,3 6,12 2,12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Property Marketing Power</h3>
            <p>Your REALTOR&reg; has the ability to list property in MLS, which syndicates to numerous other search sites such as SABOR.com, TexasRealEstate.com, and REALTOR.com — giving your property maximum exposure.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 11-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22,4 12,14.01 9,11.01"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Experience</h3>
            <p>REALTORS&reg; often handle hundreds of real estate transactions over the course of their career, giving them insight and problem-solving skills you can't get elsewhere.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="realtor-card">
            <div class="realtor-card__icon">
              <svg width="36" height="36" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FF1616" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>Objective Voice</h3>
            <p>Your REALTOR&reg; will be an objective third party who helps you stay focused on what is important to you — not emotions, pressure, or outside opinions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="sub-cta">
      <div class="sub-cta__overlay"></div>
      <div class="container" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
        <h2>Work with a REALTOR&reg; Who Puts <span class="accent">You First</span></h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I'm here to educate, serve, and deliver results. Let's talk about your goals.</p>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
          <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Let's Connect</a>
          <a href="/buyers-guide" class="btn btn-outline">Back to Buyer's Guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="faq-section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Working with a REALTOR</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>What is the difference between a real estate agent and a REALTOR?</summary>
            <p>A real estate agent is anyone who holds a valid real estate license and can legally help you buy or sell property. A REALTOR is a real estate agent who is also a member of the National Association of REALTORS and is bound by a strict Code of Ethics that goes beyond what state licensing requires. This code mandates honesty, transparency, and a fiduciary duty to put the client's interests first. When you work with a REALTOR, you have an additional layer of accountability and professionalism that protects you throughout the transaction.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>Does it cost me anything to use a buyer's agent when purchasing a home?</summary>
            <p>In most real estate transactions, the seller pays the commission for both the listing agent and the buyer's agent. This means that as a buyer, you typically receive full professional representation at no direct cost to you. Your REALTOR will handle property searches, schedule showings, negotiate on your behalf, coordinate inspections, and guide you through closing — all without charging you a fee. Not having a buyer's agent does not reduce the purchase price; it simply means no one is advocating exclusively for your interests.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>How do I choose the right REALTOR for buying a home in New Braunfels?</summary>
            <p>Look for a REALTOR who has active experience in the New Braunfels and Hill Country market, strong reviews from past clients, and a communication style that matches your preferences. Ask potential agents about their familiarity with the neighborhoods you are interested in, how many buyers they have represented in the past year, and how they handle multiple-offer situations. A good REALTOR will take the time to educate you during your first meeting without pressuring you into a commitment. Trust and local knowledge are the two most important factors.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/guadalupe-river.png" />

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the difference between a real estate agent and a REALTOR?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A real estate agent is anyone who holds a valid real estate license and can legally help you buy or sell property. A REALTOR is a real estate agent who is also a member of the National Association of REALTORS and is bound by a strict Code of Ethics that goes beyond what state licensing requires. This code mandates honesty, transparency, and a fiduciary duty to put the client's interests first. When you work with a REALTOR, you have an additional layer of accountability and professionalism that protects you throughout the transaction."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does it cost me anything to use a buyer's agent when purchasing a home?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "In most real estate transactions, the seller pays the commission for both the listing agent and the buyer's agent. This means that as a buyer, you typically receive full professional representation at no direct cost to you. Your REALTOR will handle property searches, schedule showings, negotiate on your behalf, coordinate inspections, and guide you through closing — all without charging you a fee. Not having a buyer's agent does not reduce the purchase price; it simply means no one is advocating exclusively for your interests."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do I choose the right REALTOR for buying a home in New Braunfels?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Look for a REALTOR who has active experience in the New Braunfels and Hill Country market, strong reviews from past clients, and a communication style that matches your preferences. Ask potential agents about their familiarity with the neighborhoods you are interested in, how many buyers they have represented in the past year, and how they handle multiple-offer situations. A good REALTOR will take the time to educate you during your first meeting without pressuring you into a commitment. Trust and local knowledge are the two most important factors."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ContactForm context="I'd like to work with a REALTOR for my home search..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .sub-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/hill-country-home-1.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .sub-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .sub-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .sub-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.2rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .sub-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: #FF1616; }
  .breadcrumb span { margin: 0 0.3rem; }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0 auto 3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .realtor-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .realtor-card {
    background: #fafafa;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 3px solid #FF1616;
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
  }

  .realtor-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  .realtor-card__icon {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .realtor-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .realtor-card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .sub-cta {
    position: relative;
    padding: 5rem 0;
    color: #fff;
    text-align: center;
    background-image: url('/images/testimonials-hero.jpg');
    background-size: cover;
    background-position: center;
    background-attachment: fixed;
    background-color: #333;
  }

  .sub-cta__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.65);
  }

  .sub-cta h2 { color: #fff; }

  .realtor-intro-detail {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto 2rem;
  }

  .realtor-intro-detail p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .realtor-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .sub-cta { background-attachment: scroll; }
  }
</style>
